    {{ typography.heading("Agency life", level="h3") }}

    <p class="paragraph">Having worked at an agency since 2014, I’ve had the chance to work with a variety of clients: tech giants like <strong>Apple</strong> who needed a tool to gamify the learning for call center operators; fledgling start ups like <a href="https://jumpstart.me" ref="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank"><strong>Jumpstart</strong></a>, <strong>FixFix</strong> and <strong>Veritooth</strong> looking for their vision for solving every day problems to be imagined for the web; and large enterprises like <a href="https://svclnk.com" ref="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank"><strong>ServiceLink</strong></a> who needed a brand refresh and a frontend stack&nbsp;overhaul.</p>

    <p class="paragraph">In late 2017 I began spearheading the frontend efforts to replace the existing <a href="https://fueled.com" ref="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank"><strong>fueled.com</strong></a> stack with a modern and extensible Vue.js component library to be consumed as an {% smallCaps %}NPM{% endsmallCaps %}&nbsp;package. At an agency, it’s rare to get an opportunity to work on the same project so leading the <abbr title="development">dev</abbr> effort gives the best of both&nbsp;worlds.</p>
